The paper discusses the use of energy harvesting and wireless power transfer in green radio communication networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of radio frequency (RF) in wireless power transfer, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of small-cell and Internet of Things (IoT) networks, which fall under the categories of computer architecture and robotics (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
